      SOURCE_URL=http://github.com/libuv/libuv/archive/v$VERSION/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:a6ca9f0648973d1463f46b495ce546ddcbe7cce2f04b32e802a15539e46c57ad
        WEB_SITE=http://libuv.org/
         ENTERED=20140419
         UPDATED=20160516
           SHORT="Cross-platform asychronous I/O library"

cat << EOF
Libuv is a multi-platform support library with a focus on asynchronous I/O.
It was primarily developed for use by Node.js, but it's also used by Luvit,
Julia, pyuv, and others.
Features:
  Full-featured event loop backed by epoll, kqueue, IOCP, event ports.
  Asynchronous TCP and UDP sockets.
  Asynchronous DNS resolution.
  Asynchronous file and file system operations.
  File system events.
  ANSI escape code controlled TTY.
  IPC with socket sharing, using Unix domain sockets or named pipes (Windows).
  Child processes.
  Thread pool.
  Signal handling.
  High resolution clock.
  Threading and synchronization primitives.
EOF
